  "title": "Wye Circuit",
  "body": " Wye Circuit  In a wye or star configuration, three components are connected at a common point, forming a Y shaped pattern. The common point is designated for neutral, and the three power lines, designated , , and , are connected to the free ends of the three components.  In three phase circuits, the voltage measured from line to line is called the line voltage,  , and the voltage measured across a component is called the phase voltage , .The line current , ,is the current flowing in a power line, while the phase current , , is the current flowing through a component. In a balanced system, all three line voltage are the same, as are all three line currents.  In a three-phase wye circuit,    Three inductors, wye connected    whaynes CC0     "
